'''''Chronic Respiratory Disease''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] that covers research in the field of [[respiratory disease]], including [[chronic obstructive pulmonary disease]], [[respiratory failure]], and [[obstructive sleep apnea]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Mike Morgan ([[Glenfield Hospital]]), Carolyn Rochester ([[Yale University]]), and Sally Singh ([[Glenfield Hospital]]). It was established in 2004 and is published by [[SAGE Publications]].

